F1 Ignition Fault (Boiler failed to light)
F4 Ignition Fault (Boiler went out when lit)
F6 Central Heating Flow Thermistor Fault
F10 Central Heating Return Thermistor Fault
F14 Central Heating Flow Temp Too High
F24 CH Return Temp Too High
F25 Max Temp Rise Slope to High
F26 Max Delta Temp Too Low
The main DC voltage from the SMPS is around 40V. Interesting
that the smoothing capacitors C809 & C810 are 35V working!!
Perhaps use 50V or 63V replacement caps here.
The 12V and 38V supplies are from separate secondary
windings. +5V is derived from the 12V rail. They all share
As C809 & C810 capacitors work the hardest they should
be replaced as a matter of course (with 50V or 63V working
105deg). C802 is an HV capacitor and should be replaced.
C813 is for the 12V rail and again should be replaced as it
is next to the heatsink. As should C805. All with 105deg spec
